Astro collections are useful when you want structure and flexibility at the same time.

## Why collections help

Without a schema, content fields drift over time.

With collections, frontmatter is validated at build time, and mistakes fail fast.

## Practical tip

Use a small required schema first, then expand only when a real post needs extra metadata.

For algorithm-heavy notes, this also keeps equations readable, for example $T(n)=O(n \log n)$.